{{distinguish|Majhi language}} {{Infobox language |name=Bote-Darai |altname= |nativename= |states=[[Nepal]] |region= |speakers={{sigfig|20,470|2}} |date=2011 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=Eastern? |fam5=(unclassified) |fam6=Kuswaric |lc1=bmj|ld1=Bote-Majhi |lc2=dry|ld2=Darai |glotto=bote1238 |glottoname=Bote-Majhi |glotto2=dara1250 |glottoname2=Darai }}
'''Bote''' (Bote-Majhi) and '''Darai''' are mutually intelligible tribal dialects of Nepal that are close to [[Danwar language|Danwar Rai]] but otherwise unclassified. Speakers are rapidly shifting to Nepali.
